[1] Nigeria
Date: Tue 7 Feb 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: All Africa.com & Daily Trust (Abuja) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200602070480.html>

Meningitis Kills 7 in Bauchi
-------------------------------
An outbreak of meningitis in Shira, Ganjuwa and Dass local government
areas of Bauchi state has claimed 7 lives, while 17 patients are in
critical condition in hospitals, Daily Trust investigations has
revealed.
Our correspondent, who was in Shira local government, where 11 cases
of the disease has been reported, with 4 people already dead as a
result of the infection, reports that some of the victims are lying
helplessly at the General Hospital, Yana, the headquarters of the
local government, with health personnel uncertain of what to do.
The Shira local government was said to have written a letter to the
state ministry of health for its intervention 3 weeks ago, when the
1st case was recorded, without any response from the ministry. The
chairman of the local government, Alhaji Sule Hassan Danja, was not
available to confirm the report, as he was said to have traveled to
Bauchi.
[Byline: Tashikalmah Hallah]
