[2] Kenya, Uganda
Date: Tue 7 Feb 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Yahoo News UK & Ireland [edited]
<http://uk.news.yahoo.com/07022006/323/deadly-meningitis-outbreaks-drought-stricken-kenya-uganda.html>

Deadly meningitis outbreaks in drought-stricken Kenya, Uganda
-----------------------------------------------
At least 12 people have died in the past 2 weeks from an outbreak of
meningitis in drought-stricken northern Kenya, officials said,
warning of an epidemic of the fatal disease.
Kenya's health ministry reported 57 cases of meningitis, 12 of them
fatal, since late January 2006 in West Pokot district near the border
with Uganda, which is struggling to contain an outbreak that has
killed 23 people since December 2005.
"If action is not taken, this can spread fast," said Thomas Ogaro,
head of the ministry's communicable disease division.
West Pokot, about 500 km (310 miles) northwest of Nairobi, is
inhabited by nomadic herders badly hit by the drought that threatens
millions with starvation across east Africa. Herders were forced to
move further than usual in search of water and pasture for their
livestock, which increased the chances of the illness spreading, he
said.
"The disease is rampant," Ibrahim Domongole, pastor of the Kasei
African Inland Church, told AFP, adding that at least 30 people had
died from meningitis. "The government says it is contained, but it is
not."
In neighboring Uganda, where 330 cases and 23 fatalities have been
reported in the northeast since 28 Dec 2005, the health ministry said
it had begun a mass immunization drive to stave off the spread of the
meningitis.
"We have embarked on a universal immunization of all people in (2
districts)," Dr. Sam Okware, director of health services at the
ministry told AFP, adding that 300 000 people were being targeted in
the campaign.
